Sentencas: Baln(0.3)Ti(0.7)O(2.85) (BIT07) is a new electrolyte material for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC).
Titulo: Characterisation and optimisation of the cathode/electrolyte couple for SOFC LSCF/BIT07

Sentencas: Its use with the cathode material La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) is advantageous due to their reaction (above 1000 degrees C) that leads to the formation of perovskite compounds called BLSITCFx (Ba(x)L(0.58(1-x))Sr(0.4(1-x))In(0.3)Ti(0.7)xCo(0.2(1-x))Fe(0.8(1-x))O(3-delta), with 0 <= x <= 1) at the cathode/electrolyte interface.
Titulo: Characterisation and optimisation of the cathode/electrolyte couple for SOFC LSCF/BIT07

Sentencas: In this study, the influence of the cathode microstructure on its performance has been investigated, by varying the cathode parameters.
Titulo: Characterisation and optimisation of the cathode/electrolyte couple for SOFC LSCF/BIT07

Sentencas: An area specific resistance (ASR) value of 0.07 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C has been reached and more generally the cathodes exhibit good performance (below 0.2 Omega cm(2)) for a large range of thermal treatments, cathode grain sizes and thicknesses.
Titulo: Characterisation and optimisation of the cathode/electrolyte couple for SOFC LSCF/BIT07

Sentencas: An ageing study realised at 700 degrees C for 320 h showed an ageing rate of 0.125%h(-1).
Titulo: Characterisation and optimisation of the cathode/electrolyte couple for SOFC LSCF/BIT07
